<TITLE> BNP accused of holding a 'show for the gallery' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 04 (bdnews24.com)The agriculture minister Matia Chowdhury has termed the BNP's opposition to the ministers' pay hike bill as just a "show for the gallery". The minister made the comment while refuting the allegations of the BNP in parliament on Sunday. The BNP MPs argued against increasing the pay of the ministers, state ministers and deputy ministers by saying that the cabinet members and their juniors were not performing well enough to justify a pay increase Abul Khayer Bhuiyan, a BNP MP, said the ministers should not get increased pay as they could not perform in line with people's aspirations. Asifa Ashrafi Papiya, another BNP MP said in her speech that the government could not even ensure the supply of gas, electricity and water - but it was now moving to increase salaries for the ministers. Matia Chowdhury, arguing in favour of "The ministers, ministers of state and deputy ministers (remuneration and privileges) (amendment) bill-2010", told parliament that, "The bill came to the House through the standing committee where you (the BNP MPs) agreed with it," "Since you did not oppose the bill in the standing committee, you are simply staging a show for the gallery. "Enough is enough," Matia Chowdhury said with a smile. The minister criticised the previous BNP-led government for increasing the pay of the minister on two occasions. "We have increased the ministers' pay after increasing the pay of all public servants," she said
